{"id":441,"date":"2019-02-21T11:45:15","date_gmt":"2019-02-21T01:45:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.giggsnky.com\/?p=441"},"modified":"2020-05-27T19:46:36","modified_gmt":"2020-05-27T09:46:36","slug":"vegan-vanilla-slice","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.happyveganliving.com\/vegan-vanilla-slice\/","title":{"rendered":"Vegan Vanilla Slice"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This recipe is proof that there is no dessert dish you can&#8217;t have a delicious vegan version of. The end result is both decadent and simple and will have your guests really enjoying it, or you can just eat it all yourself.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"525\" height=\"525\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/test.giggsnky.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=525%2C525\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-442\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?w=1065&amp;ssl=1 1065w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=1024%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/vanilla_slice.png?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 767px) 89vw, (max-width: 1000px) 54vw, (max-width: 1071px) 543px, 580px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption>It tastes as good as it looks&#8230;<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Serves: 10<\/strong><br><strong>Prep Time: <\/strong>20 minutes<br><strong>Cook Time: <\/strong>30&nbsp;minutes<br><strong>Total Time:<\/strong> 50 minutes (2 hours including chilling)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Ingredients <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>2 sheets&nbsp;of vegan friendly puff pastry <\/li><li>1 cup&nbsp;caster sugar <\/li><li>1\/2 cup&nbsp;vegan friendly custard powder &nbsp;<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/test.giggsnky.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/birds_custard_powder.jpg?resize=225%2C225\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-443\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/birds_custard_powder.jpg?w=225&amp;ssl=1 225w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/birds_custard_powder.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/birds_custard_powder.jpg?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption>We like to use Bird&#8217;s which we can get locally at Coles in Australia<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>\u00be cup corn flour<\/li><li>4 cups of your favourite plant-based milk <\/li><li>2 tsp&nbsp;vanilla extract <\/li><li>60 grams of Nuttelex or vegan butter substitute\/margarine   <\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"224\" height=\"224\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/test.giggsnky.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/nuttlex.jpg?resize=224%2C224\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-444\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/nuttlex.jpg?w=224&amp;ssl=1 224w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/nuttlex.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/nuttlex.jpg?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 224px) 100vw, 224px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Icing&nbsp;Ingredients<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>2 cups of icing sugar (sifted) <\/li><li>1 teaspoon Nuttelex <\/li><li>Passion fruit pulp (about 1 passion fruit) &#8211; we keep a tin in the pantry for impromptu vanilla slice *alternatively if you don\u2019t have passion fruit use 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract. <\/li><li>1 \u2013 2 teaspoons of water<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"224\" height=\"224\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/test.giggsnky.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/passionfruit.jpg?resize=224%2C224\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-446\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/passionfruit.jpg?w=224&amp;ssl=1 224w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/passionfruit.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/www.happyveganliving.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/02\/passionfruit.jpg?resize=100%2C100&amp;ssl=1 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 224px) 100vw, 224px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Method<\/strong> <\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Preheat oven to 200 C. Place the puff pastry sheets on lined oven trays. Prick with a fork and bake for 10-15 minutes at 200C or until lightly browning on top. When you remove them from the oven flatten them if they are too \u201cpuffy\u201d with a clean tea towel as you want them flat for the slice.  <\/li><li>Mix the caster sugar, cornflour and custard powder in a saucepan. Gradually add milk, whisking continually to ensure no lumps form.  <\/li><li>Add the Nuttelex\/ vegan butter mixing continuously until the custard is thick over medium \/ high heat. <\/li><li>Remove from stove top and add the vanilla.  <\/li><li>Let everything cool slightly. Place in a 22 cm square tin, first the pastry, then spread the custard evenly over the first sheet of pastry then place the second sheet of pastry on top. Place in the refrigerator.  <\/li><li>Once completely cool, make the icing and ice the slice <\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Icing<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Place icing sugar, Nuttelex (vegan butter) and passion fruit pulp in a bowl and mix. Add small amounts of water at a time until you have a medium textured spreadable icing. Spread evenly over the top of the cool slice. Only cut the slice when completely cool. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Nutritional Guide<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Amount per serving:<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"\"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Calories \/ Kilojoules<\/strong><\/td><td>471 \/ 1971<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Total<\/strong> <strong>Fat<\/strong><\/td><td>10 g<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Cholesterol<\/strong><\/td><td>0 mg<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Sodium<\/strong><\/td><td>293 mg<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Total Carbohydrate<\/strong><\/td><td>81 g<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Dietary Fibre<\/strong><\/td><td>0.1 g<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Sugars<\/strong><\/td><td>59 g<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Protein<\/strong><\/td><td>3 g<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This recipe is adapted from: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bestrecipes.com.au\/recipe\/vanilla-slice-l1483.html\">https:\/\/www.bestrecipes.com.au\/recipe\/vanilla-slice-l1483.html <\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This recipe is proof that there is no dessert dish you can&#8217;t have a delicious vegan version of. The end result is both decadent and simple and will have your guests really enjoying it, or you can just eat it all yourself.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":442,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","forma